This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with click prediction in sponsored search, which is a common problem in information retrieval. The use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN) also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to model user behavior, which could place it in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of RNNs also suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it involves analyzing user behavior on landing pages of clicked ads.
